<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-29T09:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-29T09:40:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./85: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-29T10:00:00-04:40"><hi rend="italic">June 29, 1928—10
                                    a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>39. Department’s telegram 12, June 28, 1 p.m. Dominican authorities
                                grant permission for initial flight and are favorably disposed
                                towards establishment regular service but suggest formal
                                arrangements for latter since landing facilities apparently
                                necessary.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>